column2: NA
1. Equals total household contributions and contribution supplements less benefit
payments and withdrawals; that is, net business current transfer payments for
defined benefit pension plans always equal zero.
2. Equals actual employer contributions plus imputed employer contributions plus
household actual contributions less pension service charges plus household pension
contribution supplements; see table 7.20.  All contributions to defined benefit
plans are considered to be from households.
3. Consists largely of losses by business due to fraud and unrecovered thefts,
corporate cash prizes, and payments from personal injury trust funds.
4. For detail, see table 3.7.
5. Consists of net insurance settlements paid to the rest of the world less net
insurance settlements received from the rest of the world.
